HEADWORD: Handbook
<hw>Hand"book`</hw> <pr>(-b⟦oocr⟧k`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hand</ets> + <ets>book</ets>; cf. AS.
<ets>handb⟦omac⟧c</ets>, or G. <ets>handbuch</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A book of reference, to be carried in the hand; a manual; a
guidebook.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A book containing reference information for a
specific field; <as>as, the <ex>Handbook</ex> of
Chemistry</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

